### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

compiler-cli

### Description

- Angular CLI: 17.0.3

- Feature Request: I would like Angular 17 to offer the ability to customize additionalData in the Vite configuration

- In webpack, you can configure the additionalData for SCSS like this.

```ts
module.exports = {
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.s[ac]ss$/i,
        use: [
          {
            loader: "sass-loader",
            options: {
              additionalData: "$env: " + process.env.NODE_ENV + ";",
            },
          },
        ],
      },
    ],
  },
};
```

- In Vite, you can configure the additionalData for SCSS like this.

```ts
export default {
  css: {
      preprocessorOptions: {
        scss: {
          additionalData: "$env: " + process.env.NODE_ENV + ";",
        },
      },
   },
}
```

But I've searched through the documentation and community and couldn't find a way to configure it, so I hope this feature can be provided.


### Proposed solution

Similar to `@angular-builders/custom-webpack`, it can merge configuration files in the root directory.

### Alternatives considered

Opt for a lower version when it's absolutely necessary.

### Command

build, serve

### Is this a regression?

- [X] Yes, this behavior used to work in the previous version

### The previous version in which this bug was not present was

16

### Description

In previous versions of angular, I could define packages that will not be included in the browser bundler by adding the following key to the `package.json` file:
```json
 "browser": {
    "jsonwebtoken": false,
    "password-hash": false,
    "node-fetch": false,
    "fs": false,
    "iconv-lite": false,
    "@turf/turf": false,
    "path": false
  }
```

In the new version, this setting is ignored-  and I couldn't find an alternative.
I get the following error:
```
[ERROR] TS2307: Cannot find module 'fs' or its corresponding type declarations. [plugin angular-compiler]

    src/shared/TasksController.ts:7:28:
      7 │     const fs = await import('fs');
```

My code looks like this:
```ts
  static async setAllCompleted(completed: boolean) {
    const fs = await import('fs');
    fs.writeFileSync('tmp.txt', 'hello world');
    }
```

This code is intended to run on my backend but the method itself is referred to in the frontend for my own reasons :)

When I do the same with other vite based project, I make the following change to the vite.config.ts and it works:
```ts
  build: {
    rollupOptions: {
      external: ["fs", "nodemailer", "node-fetch", "puppeteer"],
    },
  },
```

Please help

### Minimal Reproduction

Add the following code to an angular project and import it from an angular component
export class TasksController {
  static async setAllCompleted(completed: boolean) {
    const fs = await import('fs');
    fs.writeFileSync('tmp.txt', 'hello world');
  }
}


